6. Component Details

6.1 Remediation Controller

Responsible for:

- orchestrating remediation workflow
- validating remediation eligibility
- initiating config restoration
- tracking remediation result

6.2 Previous SDN Config Store

Stores:

- last valid SDN applied configuration
- configuration version history
- remediation candidate configuration

6.3 Config Reapply Workflow

Responsible for:

- pushing configuration to device
- monitoring apply status
- handling retry scenarios
- returning remediation result

6.4 Device Inventory & Connectivity Service

Responsible for:

- device identification
- connection management
- protocol handling
- credential access

6.5 Alarm Service

Responsible for:

- raising remediation alarms
- clearing resolved alarms
- generating critical alerts on remediation failure

---

7. Workflow Sequence

1. Manual configuration detected on device
2. Config Comparator Service identifies drift
3. Remediation Controller triggered
4. Previously applied SDN configuration retrieved
5. Device connectivity validated
6. Config reapply workflow initiated
7. Last valid SDN configuration pushed to device
8. Restoration result verified

If restoration succeeds:

- remediation status updated
- alarm cleared
- audit entry created

If restoration fails:

- critical alarm raised
- remediation failure logged

