10. Failure Handling

Scenario| Handling
Device unreachable| Retry remediation
Config push failure| Raise critical alarm
Previous config missing| Abort remediation
Duplicate remediation request| Deduplication handling
Validation failure| Mark remediation failed

---

11. Scalability Considerations

- Remediation workflows should support asynchronous execution
- Parallel remediation support required for multiple devices
- Workflow execution should support retry/backoff
- Remediation processing should support horizontal scaling

---

12. Security Considerations

- Remediation execution should require authorized access
- Device credentials should be securely managed
- All remediation actions must be audit logged
- Configuration restoration actions should be traceable

---

13. Assumptions

- Previously applied SDN configuration is available
- Device connectivity exists during remediation
- Config apply workflow already supported in SDN
- Drift detection framework already exists

---

